Geometric Sum

Given k, find the geometric sum using recursion i.e.
    1 + 1/2 + 1/4 + 1/8 + ... + 1/(2^k)

    Input format :
        Integer k

    Output Format :
        Geometric sum (upto 5 decimal places)

    Constraints :
        0 <= k <= 1000

    Sample Input 1 :
        3
    Sample Output 1 :
        1.87500

    Sample Input 2 :
        4
    Sample Output 2 :
        1.93750


Using Recurrsion which Involves the basic principle of PMI (Principle of Mathematical Induction)

LINKS to study for PMI:
https://byjus.com/maths/principle-of-mathematical-induction-learn-examples/



